# Dr. Zubia Mughal — Zubia Pulse Desktop
# Cursor Rules — STZ Governed Build
# Dr. Data Decision Intelligence LLC
# Every prompt follows these rules. No exceptions.

## IDENTITY

Builder: Dr. Zubia Mughal, Ed.D.
Company: Dr. Data Decision Intelligence LLC
Methodology: Skill Threshold Zone (STZ) Framework
App: Zubia Pulse Desktop — private airgapped
  decision intelligence dashboard
Repo: github.com/Zmugha1/Zubia_Pulse
Branch: dev only — never main

## TECH STACK — NEVER DEVIATE

- Tauri v2 — NEVER Electron
- React 19 + TypeScript — always
- Vite 5 — always
- Tailwind CSS v3 pinned — NEVER upgrade to v4
- shadcn/ui for components
- SQLite via tauri-plugin-sql — NEVER better-sqlite3
- Ollama via invoke('ollama_generate') —
  NEVER direct fetch() to localhost:11434
- No OpenAI API anywhere
- No Anthropic API anywhere
- No cloud database — no Supabase — no hosted DB
- No Electron — no Next.js — no server-side code
- UUID for all IDs — TEXT type — NEVER integers
- Database: zubia_pulse.db via getDb()
- App identifier: com.zubiapulse.desktop

## ARCHITECTURE RULES

- Business logic in services/ only
  NEVER in modules/ or components/
- All Ollama calls from TypeScript use invoke()
  NEVER fetch() — blocked by Tauri CSP
- All jobs go through job_queue table
  NEVER fire-and-forget
- Every action logs to audit_log
  Governance is non-negotiable
- Config in configs/ only — NEVER hardcoded
- Prompts in prompts table — NEVER hardcoded
  in TypeScript
- contact_id is TEXT/UUID — NEVER a number
- NEVER delete contacts — inactivate only
  via status = 'inactive'
- NEVER touch existing migrations
  New migrations get the next version number
  Always check schema_migrations before running
- NEVER call fetch() to localhost:11434
  Always use invoke('ollama_generate')
- Ollama model: qwen2.5:7b-instruct-q4_k_m
  num_ctx: 4096, num_predict: 1024,
  temperature: 0.1, timeout: 120s

## STZ BUILD METHODOLOGY

Every client build follows five layers:
L1 Prompts — encode how the expert thinks
L2 Skills — break expertise into named steps
L3 Agents — sequence skills into workflows
L4 Contracts — define human vs AI boundaries
L5 Evaluation — measure and improve over time

Never build without L1 answers in place.
Never ship without audit trail enabled.
Never send output without human approval gate.
Always surface model intelligence for review.
Never merge AI suggestions silently.

## BRAND COLORS — ALWAYS USE THESE

Navy:   #2D4459  sidebar, headings, dark elements
Teal:   #3BBFBF  primary action, active states
Mint:   #C8E8E5  borders, backgrounds, badges
Coral:  #F05F57  critical alerts, danger
Gold:   #C8974A  warnings, attention needed
Slate:  #7A8F95  muted text, labels, inactive
Cream:  #FEFAF6  page backgrounds
Green:  #3A7D5C  success, confirmed, paid
White:  #FFFFFF  cards, panels
LGray:  #F4F7F8  subtle backgrounds
MGray:  #E0E6E8  borders, dividers

CSS variables defined in src/styles/brand.css
Always use var(--teal) not #3BBFBF in components

## TYPOGRAPHY

Headings: Georgia, Times New Roman, serif
Body: Trebuchet MS, Segoe UI, sans-serif
Labels and metadata: Courier New, monospace
Base font size: 16px
Line height: 1.6

## WRITING RULES — ALL AI OUTPUT

- NO em dashes ever — use commas or periods
- NO generic AI language
- Every acronym explained on first use
- Every new idea needs a cited source
- Output must sound like Dr. Zubia wrote it
- Sounding like AI is the primary failure mode
- Glass box always — every output is traceable
- No black box outputs — no unsourced claims

## PROMPT DISCIPLINE

One fix per prompt.
One file per prompt.
Explicit exclusion list on every prompt.
Always end with: npx tsc --noEmit
Always git add specific files only.
NEVER git add .
Always push to dev branch only.
Always report commit hash only — nothing else.
Stop any agent that touches workflow files.

## QUALITY GATES

Before any output goes to a client:
- A output: auditable, traceable, baseline delta
- B output: transparent, correctable, improvable
- C output: black box — never ships
- Human review required on everything
- No output leaves system without approval

## GOVERNANCE

Every recommendation logged to audit_log.
Every correction logged to exceptions table.
Every prompt change versioned in prompts table.
Nothing is a black box.
Audit trail is non-negotiable.
HIPAA compliance for healthcare clients.
EU AI Act compliance for high-risk verticals.
Data never leaves the machine.
PII never in any output sent externally.
Cross-client data isolation enforced always.

## TAURI CAPABILITIES

SQL plugin: sql:default, sql:allow-load,
  sql:allow-execute, sql:allow-select
FS plugin: fs:default, fs:allow-read-text-file
Dialog plugin: dialog:default, dialog:allow-open
Never touch src-tauri/capabilities/default.json
  without explicit instruction

## WHAT NEVER TO DO

- NEVER use em dashes in any output
- NEVER call fetch() to localhost:11434
- NEVER use better-sqlite3
- NEVER upgrade Tailwind to v4
- NEVER use Electron
- NEVER use integer IDs
- NEVER hardcode prompts in TypeScript
- NEVER git add . — always specific files
- NEVER push to main branch
- NEVER delete contacts or clients
- NEVER touch existing migrations
- NEVER send output without human approval
- NEVER store PII in cloud systems
